`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
**`expect.arrayContaining` for superset assertions**: When testing that higher-level unlocks include all lower-level unlocks, `expect(higher).toEqual(expect.arrayContaining(lower))` is the idiomatic Jest pattern. It passes regardless of order and regardless of extra elements in `higher` — exactly right for an additive unlock system. Using `toEqual(lower)` would fail because the sets differ in size.
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`

